#987: Last year, I attempted suicide.  My family and friends had no idea I was suffering.  I'm receiving treatment and healing now, and though I'm still not really in a place to help anyone through their thoughts, I do need to say this: to anyone ever dealing with depression or considering suicide, please know you're not alone in the world.  I felt like I was, and I was so wrong.  So many people around you have been touched by these issues, and would be more than willing to talk or even just give you a hug when you need one.  Reach out to a friend, talk to the Counseling Center - you do have options.  Please don't give up.  Your life matters, and you deserve to live it.
